       stack.append(i)  # If stack is empty, push current index as base\n                else:\n                    max_length = max(max_length, i - stack[-1])  # Calculate the length of the current valid substring\n        \n        return max_length\n```\n\nThis solution uses a stack to keep track of the indices of the parentheses. The key idea is to use the stack to find the longest valid substring by matching each closing parenthesis with its corresponding opening parenthesis. The stack is initialized with -1 to handle the case where the entire string is a valid substring. The algorithm iterates through the string, updating the stack and calculating the maximum length of valid substrings found.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}